ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An electrocardiographic recording in which fewer than the required number of cardiac complexes are available for measurement and/or interpretation due to a shorter than planned recording or due to cardiac complexes which are present but are not suitable for measurement and/or interpretation. (CDISC)

Concepts.longName: Insufficient Number of Beats for Complete ECG Evaluation
Concepts.definition: An electrocardiographic recording in which fewer than the required number of cardiac complexes are available for measurement and/or interpretation due to a shorter than planned recording or due to cardiac complexes which are present but are not suitable for measurement and/or interpretation. (CDISC)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Persistent Atrial Flutter
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An electrocardiographic finding of atrial flutter which is present during the entire recording.

Concepts.longName: Persistent Atrial Flutter
Concepts.definition: An electrocardiographic finding of atrial flutter which is present during the entire recording.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Paroxysmal Atrial Flutter
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An electrocardiographic finding of atrial flutter which occurs intermittently during the recording. Other rhythms which may be present are sinus rhythm, junctional rhythm, or an atrial paced rhythm.

Concepts.longName: Paroxysmal Atrial Flutter
Concepts.definition: An electrocardiographic finding of atrial flutter which occurs intermittently during the recording. Other rhythms which may be present are sinus rhythm, junctional rhythm, or an atrial paced rhythm.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Supraventricular Bigeminy by ECG Finding
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An electrocardiographic finding of a supraventricular QRS complex followed by a premature supraventricular complex for 3 or more consecutive cycles; a regularly irregular rhythm of normal and abnormal QRS complexes in a 1-1 ratio. (CDISC)

Concepts.longName: Supraventricular Bigeminy by ECG Finding
Concepts.definition: An electrocardiographic finding of a supraventricular QRS complex followed by a premature supraventricular complex for 3 or more consecutive cycles; a regularly irregular rhythm of normal and abnormal QRS complexes in a 1-1 ratio. (CDISC)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Supraventricular Trigeminy by ECG Finding
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An electrocardiographic finding of two supraventricular QRS complexes followed by a premature supraventricular complex for 3 or more consecutive cycles; a regularly irregular rhythm of normal and abnormal QRS complexes in a 2-1 ratio. (CDISC)

Concepts.longName: Supraventricular Trigeminy by ECG Finding
Concepts.definition: An electrocardiographic finding of two supraventricular QRS complexes followed by a premature supraventricular complex for 3 or more consecutive cycles; a regularly irregular rhythm of normal and abnormal QRS complexes in a 2-1 ratio. (CDISC)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Sustained Atrial Tachycardia by ECG Finding
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An electrocardiographic finding of an atrial tachycardia that lasts 30 seconds or longer.

Concepts.longName: Sustained Atrial Tachycardia by ECG Finding
Concepts.definition: An electrocardiographic finding of an atrial tachycardia that lasts 30 seconds or longer.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Non-Sustained Accelerated Idioventricular Rhythm by ECG Finding
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An electrocardiographic finding of idioventricular rhythm with a rate greater than 50 beats per minute that terminates in less than 30 seconds.

Concepts.longName: Non-Sustained Accelerated Idioventricular Rhythm by ECG Finding
Concepts.definition: An electrocardiographic finding of idioventricular rhythm with a rate greater than 50 beats per minute that terminates in less than 30 seconds.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Sustained Accelerated Idioventricular Rhythm by ECG Finding
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An electrocardiographic finding of idioventricular rhythm with a rate greater than 50 beats per minute that lasts 30 seconds or longer.

Concepts.longName: Sustained Accelerated Idioventricular Rhythm by ECG Finding
Concepts.definition: An electrocardiographic finding of idioventricular rhythm with a rate greater than 50 beats per minute that lasts 30 seconds or longer.
